Classes
Class
Description
Athlete
Athlete The athlete class is the constructor for all of the athletes in the game.
AthleteDatabase
AthleteDatabase The athlete database is where an athlete is created.
AthleteDisplay
athleteDisplay This extension of JPanel is used throughout the game to visually represent an athlete and their stats.
ClubSetup
clubSetup This method is responsible for setting up the club page.
FinishPanel
FinishPanel This is the finishing screen panel created after either all the weeks have finished, the user want's to quit the game or they cannot afford a new player.
GameEnvironment
Game Environment The game environment class initializes all the main code based classes (not swing) in the code by calling them in a specific order as per requirements before passing the initialized classes into the mainFrame class, creating the JFrame
GoalEvents
Goal Events This class contains a set of strings in an array list that are called whenever your team and the opposition score a goal
HomePanel
HomePanel This is the main panel of the program, created after the club setup has been done.
ItemDisplay
ItemDisplay This extension of JPanel is what is used in the store and the TeamViewPanel in order to see a visual representation of purchaseableItem.
MainFrame
mainFrame This extension of JFrame is the main window in which the game runs.
MatchRunner
matchRunner This class is where the matches are simulated.
OpposingTeam
opposingTeam An extension of the PlayerClub, an OpposingTeam auto name generation.
OtherEvents
otherEvents otherEvents contains a string of the possible events called in the matchRunner which do not result in a goal.
PlayerClub
Player Club This class is responsible for creating the framework for the player club.
PlayerDatabase
playerDatabase This class contains a string of all possible default names for players in the game.
PurchaseableAthletes
PurchaseableAthletes This class contains a hashtable of random players that are used in the creation of the store and its refreshing.
PurchaseableItem
PurchaseableItem PurchaseableItem is the class of the items that can be applied to each player in a team.
PurchaseableItems
PurchaseableItems PurchaseableItems contains a hashtable of the 3 types of purchaseable items in the game: Active recovery, Attack Training, and Defense Training.
Stadium
Stadium Stadium is the object that contains all the stats about the player's club and holds the hadhtable for the possible opponents.
StadiumPanel
StadiumPanel StadiumPanel is the JPanel which allows the user to select an opposition team and begin a match.
Store
Store is the object which contains the purchasable Players and the purchasable Items.
StorePanel
StorePanel StorePanel is the JPanel where the store can be accessed.
TeamDatabase
teamDatabase teamDatabase is the class from which the random team names are generated.
TeamViewPanel
TeamViewPanel The TeamViewPanel is the JPanel from which all intra-team actions can take place.
